>>66148728
I enjoy sad stories, but in hindsight it isn't a great game/story. I give it a 5/10. Here's my breakdown

+Visual storytelling
Wow, perhaps the game's best quality. EE wanted to tell a story and that's exactly what he did. It's clear that the world was thought about, even at times where it is ambiguous to the viewer what exactly happened. Ambiguity in artwork is great.
+Unafraid to be a tragedy.
People have talked about this enough already. I'm glad the creator decided to avoid feeding the fish in favor of plot.
+Depth of characters
They all feel like real people with real problems that may or may not be resolved. No one is trying to be a cute and marketable plushie.

Cons:
-The sound design really sucked.
The generic horror drone gets old really quickly, and aside from the scene in A2 and ventilation there isn't any contrast. I had to turn that crap off after a while.
Sound mixing was objectively poor. Footsteps too loud as well as some other effects.
What you needed to do was make a warm and friendly theme for wolf's room. That way the player relaxes when talking to her. That way there's contrast between that and seeing Lizard and Eagle practically dead.
-Mood clashes.
Sometimes the expressions are played for laughs, but the situation at hand is very serious and the music hasn't changed. Just feels like the "impression" of comedy. I never laughed when I played this game despite some honest efforts by EE.
-Plot holes
1.You've known Wolf for 10 years in this tiny space and you didn't know that she was a geographer? Bullshit. That's a long-ass time to not seek human connection.
2. I still don't know why the door to the main entrance was closed for the first 2 days. Rat wasn't barricading it, right? It opened without issue on day 3 so it feels like some Deus ex machina level convenience.

What do you rate bunkergame?
